# sky_core Editing Rules

## Event Bus
- `sky_event_bus_config_t`: `max_subscribers=32`, `queue_size=16`, `async=true`
- Handlers called **outside** mutex to prevent deadlocks
- Async mode copies payload via `malloc`; keep event data small (<64 bytes)
- Never block in an event handler

## Registry
- `sky_service_id_t` = `const char *` (e.g. `"sky_stepper"`, `"sky_wifi"`)
- Lifecycle: `init(config)` → `start()` → `stop()` → `deinit()`
- `start_all` calls init then start in registration order; `stop_all` reverses

## Config (NVS)
- `sky_config_init()` handles `nvs_flash_init` + erase-on-corrupt
- Namespace max 15 chars; key max 15 chars (NVS constraint)

## Crash Safety
- `sky_crash_register(service_id, &crash_config)` per component
- `safe_state_handler` runs in ISR context — no malloc, no logging, no FreeRTOS calls
- `sky_error_report` with `SKY_SEVERITY_FATAL` auto-triggers crash handler

## Events Range
| Range | Owner |
|-------|-------|
| 0x0000–0x00FF | Core |
| 0x0100–0x01FF | Stepper |
| 0x0200–0x027F | Network/Matter |
| 0x0280–0x02FF | OTA |
| 0x0300–0x03FF | Power |
